;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 22px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); letter-spacing: normal;"><strong>Manual Payments&nbsp;</strong></h2><p><strong>Bank Transfer :&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Accept payments through a bank transfer to your account.&nbsp;In this way, you put your bank account data and when the customer selects at the checkout page this payment method will be showing with him your bank account and able transferred to it.</p><p><strong>Cheque or Purchase Order :&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Accept payments through a banking check or a certified purchase order.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Cash on Delivery :&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Accept payments in cash when you deliver the products to your customers. If your store customer selects this payment method, they should pay for the order not when it is placed, but when it is delivered.</p><p><strong>Free Checkout :&nbsp;</strong></p><div class="caption"><p>The order will be made without payment from the customers side.</p><h2 style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.53846; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 0px; font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: normal;"><strong>Prepaid Cards</strong></h2><div><p>Some providers are offering this service such ( CashU, OneCard, Zain Cash)</p><h2 style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.53846; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 0px; font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: normal;"><strong>Mobile Payment</strong></h2><div><p>By using a mobile service provider to pay the order like (MobiPay)</p></div></div></div></div></div>
